================================================================================

THIRD-PARTY LIBRARIES

As of Phase 2, WaveEdit uses only the JUCE framework and standard C++ libraries.
When additional open source libraries are integrated (Phase 3+), they will be
documented here with full attribution including:
- Library name and version
- Copyright holder
- License type
- Homepage/repository URL

For full license texts, see the Licenses/ directory.

================================================================================

FUTURE LIBRARY INTEGRATIONS (Phase 4+)

The following libraries are planned for integration with proper attribution:

- libsamplerate (BSD-2-Clause) - Sample rate conversion
- FFTW or Kiss FFT (GPL v2+ / BSD-3-Clause) - FFT for spectrum analyzer
- libebur128 (MIT) - EBU R128 loudness metering
- RNNoise (BSD-3-Clause) - Noise suppression
- Rubber Band Library (GPL v2+) - Pitch/time stretching
- LAME (LGPL) - MP3 encoding
- libFLAC (BSD-3-Clause) - FLAC codec
- libvorbis (BSD-3-Clause) - Ogg Vorbis codec
- Opus (BSD-3-Clause) - Opus codec
- VST3 SDK (GPL v3) - VST3 plugin hosting

All licenses are compatible with GPL v3.

